{"questionId":"14474633","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows part of the graphs of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/755d05bf1b3ef9870778030147ec40a0d2429056.png\"></p>\n<p>The graphs intersect at&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>p</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mi>q</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>discriminant&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>d</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>recognizing discriminant&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp; &nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;</strong></em>OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>d</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>36</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>d</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14474633","referenceCode":"23N.1.SL.TZ2.8bii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence show that d2-9d>0.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.4—Key features of graphs, intersections using technology","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.7—Solutions of quadratic equations and inequalities, discriminant and nature of roots","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.9—Exponential and logarithmic functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
